On May 4, 2020, the government of Aragon implemented hygiene measures as the region enters phase 0 of the deescalation plan. 

In this phase 0...

-The use of a mask is mandatory in public transport - bus, rail, metro, maritime, air and taxi-, whose occupancy should not exceed 50%, and the mask is recommended for all types of activities outside the home; 

- Working people who have symptoms related to COVID-19 or who are in quarantine will not be able to attend their jobs;

- Clients may not use the stores' toilets "except when strictly necessary." In this case, the toilets, taps and doorknobs will be cleaned immediately. All establishments and premises must also have bins, if possible with a lid and pedal, in which to deposit tissues and any other disposable material, which must be cleaned frequently and at least once a day; 

- Shops of up to 400 square meters will have to maintain a minimum distance of 2 meters, from one if separation systems such as screens or glass are used. These establishments must also be disinfected twice a day - with "special attention" to the most frequent contact surfaces such as doorknobs, counters, furniture handrails- discard the materials used and the protective equipment and must have dispensers of hydroalcoholic gel. The workers will have to wash their work clothes every day between 60 and 90 degrees of temperature. An opening hours or a preferential corridor will be established for people over 65 years of age.

