On March 21, 2020, The government of Aragon announced new health administrative configuration. The different elderly centers, in which cases of contagion of coronavirus have been detected, will have a reference professional of the Aragon Health System that will monitor the evolution of the situation of the center and the adoption of the following measures; 

-The referral of residents in centers for the elderly and centers for people with disabilities to special care facilities, in cases where the conditions of the center do not allow their adequate isolation and in the case when it concern people affected by coronavirus, both confirmed and positive or suspected with an epidemiological link, or people with a hospital discharge who require a period of 14 days of quarantine; 

- The referral of each case will be indicated by those responsible for public health and will be carried out without the need for authorization from the affected person, communicating the decision to both the displaced resident and, where appropriate, the responsible family member or corresponding legal representative;

- The planned referral will be carried out both in centers whose structure and organization do not allow adequate zoning for the correct isolation of patients, as well as in centers whose high percentage of occupancy advises such transfer and those in which , as indicated by the Occupational Risk Prevention Service, the temporary separation from the service has been indicated.

From March 15 2020 until March 29 2021, Aragon is enforcing a restriction and regulation of businesses by suspending the activity of the following public establishments ; 

- All kinds of bars, pubs, clubs and cafeteria; 
- All restaurants and cafe;
- Theaters and movie theaters;
- Conference rooms, exposition rooms and party rooms;
- Amusement parks and fairs;  
- Playgrounds;
- Circus; 
- Sports facilities.
- Museums;
- Libraries;
- Recreational halls, game rooms, bingo halls and casinos;
- Unregulated public establishments.

Exception : Bars, cafes and restaurants, provided they are closed to the public, may provide home delivery services for food.

