From May 4, 2020, as Aragon enters the phase 0 of the deescalation plan, new restrictions and regulations of business are put in place in the province of Aragon. This represent an easing of the previous mesures.

- Restaurants and cafes will be able to serve take away orders. Consumption inside the premises is still prohibited and the establishments may only remain open to the public during order collection hours;

- Small shops, hairdressers, beauty centers, physiotherapy, podiatry and dentists may open but provided they have an appointment for individual care; 

- Any business of less than 400 meters, be it a shop or a professional service, will be opened to the public. It will be required to maintain a minimum distance of 2 meters and respect strong sanitary measures and several restrictions;

-Professional athletes who will be able to do individual training outdoors. Those who practice adapted or paralympic sports modalities may have the accompaniment of another person to carry out their sporting activity. In both cases, a coach may be present who may not get closer than two meters and will have to wear a mask. When the sport involves the use of bicycles or skates, the safety distance will be ten meters.

