On May 11, as Aragon enters the phase 1 of the deescalation plan, the government of Aragon implemented new restrictions and regulations of Businesses. They represent an easing of the previous measures. 

- Stores of less than 400 square meters will open with a maximum capacity of 30%, while large stores such as Puerto Venecia or Grancasa will remain closed until phase 2; 

- Cafes, bars and restaurants will no longer be open solely to pick up orders. From today it is possible to sit on a terrace without a time limit, but with a minimum separation of two meters between clients. Up to 50% of the tables are allowed, although several municipalities have already announced that they will be able to occupy pedestrian and parking areas.

